    "headline": "Apple Now Makes About 25% of iPhones in India After China Pivot",
    "summary": "The company assembled about 55 million iPhones in India in 2025, up from 36 million a year earlier, people familiar with the matter said, asking not to be named because the numbers aren’t public.  Apple makes about 220 million to 230 million iPhones a year globally, with India’s share of the total increasing rapidly.  Apple has accelerated its expansion in the world’s most populous country in recent years, bolstered by Prime Minister Narendra Modi’s production-linked incentives aimed at turning India into the world’s factory.",
